                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, July 8 (PTI): A Delhi court today framed charges of murder and rioting against senior Congress leader Sajjan Kumar and others in connection with a 1984 anti-Sikh riot case. Six people were killed in the riot in Sultanpuri here.          
	The court has also framed charges against Kumar and four others for the offence of spreading enmity between two communities. The framing of charges paves the way for initiation of a criminal trial.                  
	Chennai (PTI): Madras High Court has asked the Centre to allow slain LTTE leader Prabhakarans mother, Parvathiammal, to undergo medical treatment in India whenever she wanted to do so. The external affairs ministry has, however, asked her to defer the visit.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The railways today decided to postpone the forthcoming railway recruitment board examination scheduled for July 25.          
	The decision was taken in the wake of a CBI investigation into the alleged multi crore job-scam unearthed last month.                   
	 Guwahati: A blast occurred on a railway bridge in Assams Sonitpur district on Wednesday night. The Ranjan Daimary faction of the National Democratic Front of Boroland is suspected to have carried out the explosion. Police said the blast damaged the railway track. Several trains have been cancelled or diverted.                                                                                                                                              
